"title": "8413: edification",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8413",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The building up and strengthening in the faith of believers and churches. Believers are strengthened by God and are urged, too, to build up one another. The church is edified through God's word, through the Holy Spirit and the proper use of spiritual gifts, through the church's appointed ministries and through the mutual love, support and encouragement of its members.</p>\n<h2>God edifies his people by strengthening them</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:29-Isa40:31\">ISA 40:29–40:31</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:16\">EZK 34:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps29:11\">PSA 29:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:26\">PSA 73:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:11\">ISA 40:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:10\">ISA 41:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:16-2Thess2:17\">2TH 2:16–2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:3\">2TH 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:9\">HEB 13:9</a></p>\n<h2>The edification of believers</h2>\n<h3>God builds up the community of faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:4-1Pet2:5\">1PE 2:4–2:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer24:6-Jer24:7\">JER 24:6–24:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:4\">JER 31:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer42:10\">JER 42:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:19-Eph2:22\">EPH 2:19–2:22</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are to build themselves up</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:20\">JUD 1:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:6-Col2:7\">COL 2:6–2:7</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are to build one another up</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:2\">ROM 15:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:19\">ROM 14:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:29\">EPH 4:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:13\">HEB 3:13</a></p>\n<h2>The means of edification</h2>\n<h3>God's word</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:32\">ACT 20:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:28\">PSA 119:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:20\">ROM 4:20</a> <em>Abraham was strengthened in his faith by his acceptance of God's promise</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:4\">ROM 15:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:15-2Tim3:17\">2TI 3:15–3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:2\">1PE 2:2</a></p>\n<h3>The Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:16\">EPH 3:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:31\">ACT 9:31</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual gifts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:26\">1CO 14:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:11\">ROM 1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:7\">1CO 12:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:3-1Cor14:4\">1CO 14:3–14:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:12\">1CO 14:12</a></p>\n<h3>Appointed ministries</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11-Eph4:12\">EPH 4:11–4:12</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:15\">JER 3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:4\">JER 23:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:4\">EZK 34:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech11:16\">ZEC 11:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:41\">ACT 15:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:23\">ACT 18:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:19\">2CO 12:19</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:4-Acts16:5\">ACT 16:4–16:5</a> <em>The message from the Jerusalem apostles results in believers being strengthened.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:8\">2CO 10:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:10\">2CO 13:10</a></p>\n<h3>Love and encouragement</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:15-Eph4:16\">EPH 4:15–4:16</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:11\">1TH 5:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:12\">ROM 1:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:20-Rom14:21\">ROM 14:20–14:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:1\">1CO 8:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:10-1Cor8:13\">1CO 8:10–8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:23-1Cor10:24\">1CO 10:23–10:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:12-Heb12:13\">HEB 12:12–12:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:3-Isa35:4\">ISA 35:3–35:4</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of those who edified others</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut3:28\">DEU 3:28</a> <em>Moses</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job4:3-Job4:4\">JOB 4:3–4:4</a> <em>Job</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:1-Isa40:2\">ISA 40:1–40:2</a> <em>Isaiah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:32\">LUK 22:32</a> <em>Simon Peter</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:22\">ACT 14:22</a> <em>Paul and Barnabas</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:32\">ACT 15:32</a> <em>Judas and Silas</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:2\">1TH 3:2</a> <em>Timothy</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:7\">PHM 1:7</a> <em>Philemon</em></p>\n<h2>The goal of edification</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:13\">EPH 4:13</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:14\">EPH 4:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:9-Phil1:10\">PHP 1:9–1:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:14\">HEB 5:14</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:13\">1TH 3:13</a> <em>Edification results in right living.</em></p>",
